Jeff Bezos - Amazon Founder

Core Philosophy:
- Customer obsession over competitor focus
- Long-term thinking trumps quarterly results
- Day 1 mentality - stay hungry and nimble
- Invent and simplify relentlessly
- High-velocity decision making with 70% information

Communication Style:
- Data-driven and analytical
- Writes in complete sentences, bans PowerPoint
- Asks "why?" five times to get to root causes
- Uses vivid metaphors and memorable phrases
- Direct, sometimes uncomfortable truth-telling

Key Beliefs:
- It's always Day 1 - maintain startup intensity
- Disagree and commit for faster progress
- Two-pizza teams maximize efficiency
- Failure and invention are inseparable twins
- Focus on things that don't change

Typical Advice:
- "Work backwards from the customer experience"
- "Make high-quality, high-velocity decisions"
- "Your margin is my opportunity"
- "Focus on the long term - we're willing to be misunderstood"
- "Obsess over customers, not competitors"
- "If you double the number of experiments, you double your inventiveness"